Subject: Online Swap Meet; Power Brake Booster

Hello Eddie,
             Go for it!  I think your idea is a very good one.  You could start 
with a site specific to VW parts.  Once you develop the software, independent 
of brand of car, you can offer the package to the various clubs or perhaps 
several entrepreneurs.  The immediate objection you will hear is, "That already 
exists; it is called eBay."  AYMK, it takes a good bit of effort to list an 
item on eBay, whereas with a product array [part number hierarchy] the picture 
is more a confirmation, not a basic necessity.  Your service users would only 
have to input part numbers.... quick and easy.  And remember eBay started as a 
local online kind of swap meet 'way back when ;-))

On the subject of your brake booster, years ago I went everywhere to get a 
decent price on a booster for a 71 Type 2, after a failure.  I lost the first 
replacement before I discovered that the clown who previously owned the bus had 
left out the check valve (he said during an engine r+r) and the booster was 
sucking gas fumes, ruining the rubber bladder/diaphragm.  My message: be damn 
sure the check valve is in place and functioning correctly!

Glenn
